<p>
	Our macadamia oil is rich in mono-unsaturated oils, oleic and palmitic acids. It is a highly emollient oil and beneficial to all skin types to promote skin suppleness. Macadamia oil is quickly absorbed into the skin making it particularly good for dry or wrinkled skin and it is used to help prevent premature aging.</p>
<p>
	Macadamia oil can be used on its own or add a small amount to any massage oil to promote skin suppleness. Macadamia oil is also an excellent hair oil and widely used for treating a dry or itchy scalp.</p>
<p>
	Macadamia trees grow from 50 to 60 feet high with long, narrow leaves and clusters of pink or white flowers. The round, hard-shelled nuts grow in clusters and are covered with the husks that split when they are ripe.</p>
